{"title_page": "Mackenzie Aladjem", "text_new": "{{short description|American actress}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Mackenzie Aladjem\n| image              = \n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = Mackenzie Elizabeth Aladjem\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|2001|09|11}}\n| birth_place        = [[Burbank, California]], U.S.\n| residence          =\n| occupation \u00a0       = Actress, dancer\n| years_active       = 2007\u2013present\n| website            = \n}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{BLP primary sources|date=September 2018}}\n\n'''Mackenzie Elizabeth Aladjem''' (born September 11, 2001)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm2662815/bio?ref_=nm_ov_bio_sm|title=Mackenzie Aladjem - Biography - IMDb|website=imdb.com}}</ref> is an American actress and dancer. She co-starred in the Showtime series ''[[Nurse Jackie]]'' as the [[title character]]'s daughter, Fiona Peyton, for which she won a [[Young Artist Award]]. She also is appearing in the soap opera ''[[All My Children]]'' as [[Miranda Montgomery]].\n\n==Career==\nAladjem has appeared in television shows including ''[[Nurse Jackie]]'' and ''[[All My Children]]''. She has also performed in the national tour of the Broadway stage production of ''[[Annie (musical)|Annie]]'' portraying the character Molly. Aladjem has been performing since age four.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100124172432/http://www.annieontour.com/cast/sydney-richardson.html|title=Annie on Tour - Cast - MACKENZIE ALADJEM|website=web.archive.org}}</ref>  She made her film debut in the film ''[[The Lincoln Lawyer (film)|The Lincoln Lawyer]]'', based on the book by [[Michael Connelly]].\n\n==Personal life==\nAladjem was raised Jewish, and her father is from Uruguay. She attended [[Burbank High School (Burbank, California)|Burbank High School]] and participated on the school's varsity dance team, graduating in 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/socal/burbank-leader/news/tn-blr-me-choreography-contest-20180124-story.html|title=Burbank High School student wins at dance competition|website=latimes.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bioagewho.co/mackenzie-aladjem-bio-wiki-age-height-net-worth-career-parents-family/|title=Mackenzie Aladjem Bio, Wiki, Age, Height, Net Worth, Career, Parents, Family|website=bioagewho.co}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Film !! Role !! Notes\n|-\n| rowspan=3 | 2007 || ''[[CSI: Miami]]'' || Emma Wade || Television series (Episode: \"Born to Kill\")\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | ''[[Passions]]'' || rowspan=2 | Pamela || Television soap opera (Episode: #1.2000)\n|-\n| Television soap opera (Episode: #1.2001)\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | 2010 || ''[[Nurse Jackie]]'' || Fiona Peyton || Main Character, 2010\u20132015\n|-\n| ''[[All My Children]]'' || [[Miranda Montgomery]] || Television soap opera, July 2010\u2013July 2011\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | 2011 || ''[[The Lincoln Lawyer (film)|The Lincoln Lawyer]]'' || Hayley Haller || Film debut\n|-\n| ''[[Workaholics]]'' || Girl #2 || Television series (Episode: \"Heist School\")\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | 2012 || ''[[This Is 40]]'' || Judith ||\n|-\n| ''[[Of Two Minds]]'' || Mollie Clarke || Television movie\n|-\n|| 2013 || ''[[Grey's Anatomy]]'' || Emma || Television series (Episode: \"Idle Hands\")\n|-\n|| 2016 || ''[[Time Toys]]'' || Jenny Johnstone || Film\n|-\n| 2016 || ''[[Criminal Minds]]'' || Lily || Television series (Episode: \"Hostage\")\n|-\n|| 2017 || ''[[Hawaii Five-0 (2010 TV series)|Hawaii Five-0]]'' || Moani amosa/Tanya morrison || Television series (Episode: \"exodus-S7ep19\")\n|}\n\n==Awards==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Award !! Category !! Film !! Result\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2011<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.youngartistawards.org/noms32.html |title=32nd Annual Young Artist Awards |publisher=youngartistawards.org |accessdate=July 26, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130808150433/http://www.youngarti