/en-US/home}}\n\n{{Epic Games}}\n\n[[Category:Fortnite| ]]\n[[Category:Epic Games]]\n[[Category:IOS games]]\n[[Category:Nintendo Switch games]]\n[[Category:Online games]]\n[[Category:PlayStation 4 games]]\n[[Category:Windows games]]\n[[Category:Xbox One games]]\n[[Category:MacOS games]]\n[[Category:Unreal Engine games]]\n[[Category:2010s fads and trends]]\n[[Category:2020s fads and trends]]\n", "name_user": "Hi im MaLwArE", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fortnite"}
{"title_page": "Torbj\u00f8rn C. Pedersen", "text_new": "{{short description|Danish tourist, traveller and adventurer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n|name=Torbj\u00f8rn C. Pedersen\n|image=Torbjorn_C._Pedersen_in_Fiji.jpg\n|caption=Pedersen in Fiji, December 2019\n|birth_place=[[Kerteminde]], [[Denmark]]\n|birth_date=19 December 1978<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.onceuponasaga.dk/images/Pictures/_new/254/bula.jpg|title=Torbj\u00f8rn C. Pedersen is nicknamed Thor. In Fiji, December 2019.|website=Once Upon a Saga}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''Torbj\u00f8rn C. \"Thor\" Pedersen''' (born 19 December, 1978) is a Danish traveller and adventurer known for the '''''Once Upon a Saga''''' project: a journey to visit every country in the world without the use of air travel. The project has lasted for over six years, and Pedersen had, {{As of|2020|04|3|lc=y}}, visited 194 of the planned 203 nations.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/onceuponasaga/|title=onceuponasaga|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2020-01-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.onceuponasaga.dk/blog/345-negotiating-the-death-toll|title=Negotiating the death toll|last=Pedersen|first=Torbj\u00f8rn C.|website=www.onceuponasaga.dk|language=en-gb|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/travel/article/around-the-world-without-flying/index.html|title=This man is just 9 countries away from visiting every nation in the world without flying. But he's stuck in Hong Kong due to Covid-19|first=Kate |last=Springer|website=CNN|language=en|access-date=2020-04-29}}</ref>\n\n== Early life ==\nTorbj\u00f8rn Cederl\u00f6f Pedersen was born in Kerteminde, Denmark, to Torben Pedersen (Danish) and Ylva Cederl\u00f6f (Finnish). The family moved to Vancouver, Canada, then to Toronto, Canada, and  after that to New Jersey, USA over a period of six years, before returning to Denmark in 1984 where he spent his childhood growing up in Kerteminde and Bryrup before entering business school at Silkeborg Handelsskole, Silkeborg. Pedersen graduated as a merchant student in 1998 and was drafted to the military later the same year, serving as a royal life guard at the royal palaces throughout Denmark. He was later a UN soldier for half a year in Eritrea and Ethiopia. Following an education in shipping and logistic the Dane worked several years abroad in Libya, Bangladesh, Kazahkstan, Azerbaijan, the United States and other countries. When travelling abroad, Torbj\u00f8rn is nicknamed Thor.\n\n== Once Upon a Saga ==\nIn 2013, Pedersen began planning a project which aimed at visiting every country in the world in a single unbroken journey explicitly without the use of air transport.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lonelyplanet.com/news/2016/12/30/travelling-world-no-planes/|title=This man is travelling the world without ever getting on a plane|last=|first=|website=Lonely Planet News|language=en|access-date=2019-05-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/leifwalcutt/2017/02/14/around-the-world-by-container-ship-one-mans-quest-to-visit-every-country/|title=Around The World By Container Ship: One Man's Quest To Visit Every Country|last=Walcutt|first=Leif|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2019-05-18}}</ref> [[Graham Hughes]] holds the world record of fastest visiting all countries by public surface transport, according to [[Guinness World Records]]. Hughes was however permitted to fly home to Britain twice during his journey, as long as he returned to the same airport in order to continue his journey. To visit every country in the world, in one single journey, without catching a single flight is something that has never been done before.<ref name=\"The National\">Leve, Andy [https://amp.thenational.ae/lifestyle/travel/torbjorn-pedersen-the-man-on-a-mission-to-visit-every-country-in-the-world-without-taking-a-single-flight-1.907263 \"Torbjorn Pedersen: the man on a mission to visit every country in the world, without taking a single flight\"], ''The National'', Abu Dhabi, 7 September 2019. <!--accessed 08 January 2020--></ref>\n\nThrough the project Pedersen intends to reach every country without flying, while promoting every country and the world in a positive way.\n\nOn 10 October, 2013 at 10:10am (10/10,10:10) '''''Once Upon a Saga''''' began at Dybb\u00f8l M\u00f8lle in Southern Denmark. Soon after Pedersen crossed into Germany by train and had, in January 2020, reached 193 of the intended 203 countries<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.onceuponasaga.dk/blog/330-mv-kota-hakim-passenger-no-1-reaching-marshall-islands-the-hard-way|title=MV \"Kota Hakim\" \u2013 passenger no. 1 (reaching Marshall Islands the hard way)|last=Pedersen|first=Torj\u00f8rn|date=2019-12-30|work=Once Upon a Saga|access-date=2020-01-01|language=en-GB}}</ref> on all six inhabited continents without returning home.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vice.com/en_us/article/8qgv3k/kakovo-eto-povidat-mir-prakticheski-besplatno-puteshestvuya-na-kontejnernyh-sudah|title=What It's Like to See the World for Almost No Money by Traveling on Container Ships|last=Pearl|first=Mike|date=2016-12-12|website=Vice|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2014/dec/14/wanderlust-viking-cheap-travel-aeroplane-free-visit-every-country|title=Wanderlust Viking: my aeroplane-free aim to visit every country on \u00a312 a day|last=Russell|first=Helen|date=2014-12-14|work=The Guardian|access-date=2019-05-18|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref>\n\nHe was originally expected to complete the project and return to Denmark again in 2020 after visiting his last country, the Maldives, in October 2020.<ref name=\"Midtjyllands Avis\">Andersen, Mette [https://www.midtjyllandsavis.dk/artikel/1c992215-593b-4bab-aa1b-9df8244f6693/ \"Eventyrer har lang vej hjem\"], ''Midtjyllands Avis'', Silkeborg, 4 January 2020. <!--accessed 08 January 2020--></ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Travel/danish-man-travels-world-20-day/story?id=26995531|title=How This Man Travels the World on Just $20 a Day|website=ABC News|language=en|access-date=2019-05-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.news.com.au/travel/world-travel/danish-traveller-torbjorn-c-pedersen-travels-the-world-on-just-20-a-day/news-story/556c52b6292ff2be7b8840be1ba94cd2|title=How to travel the world without using one plane|date=2014-11-17|website=NewsComAu|access-date=2019-05-18}}</ref> However, {{As of|2020|April|lc=y}}, he has been stuck in Hong Kong for several months due to the [[COVID-19 epidemic]].<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nThe long journey has earned Pedersen media coverage in more than 100 countries so far.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.onceuponasaga.dk/press|title=Press|last=Salquist|first=Ann-Christina|date=2014-12-14|work=Once Upon a Saga|access-date=2020-01-01|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref name=\"Borneo Bulletin\">[https://borneobulletin.com.bn/danish-globetrotter-finds-bruneians-absolute-sweethearts-2/ \"Danish globetrotter finds Bruneians \u2018absolute sweethearts\u2019\"], ''Borneo Bulletin'', Bandar Seri Begawan, 20 July 2019. <!--accessed 16 January 2020--></ref><ref name=\"Kuwait Bazaar\">[https://bazaar.town/thor-once-upon-a-saga/ \"ONLY NINETEEN MORE THOR!\"], ''Kuwait Bazaar'', Kuwait, 1 July 2019. <!--accessed 16 January 2020--></ref><ref name=\"The New Paper\">[https://www.tnp.sg/news/singapore/he-journeys-across-world-without-flying-red-cross \"He journeys across the world without flying for the Red Cross\"], ''The New Paper'', Singapore, 21 June 2019. <!--accessed 16 January 2020--></ref><ref name=\"CNTraveler India\">[https://www.cntraveller.in/story/name-thor-hes-travelling-around-world-without-flying/ \"His name is Thor and he\u2019s travelling around the world without flying\"], ''Cond\u00e9 Nast Traveler India'', Mumbai, 2 February 2019. <!--accessed 16 January 2020--></ref><ref name=\"Online Raftar\">[https://www.onlineraftar.com/2019/01/30/26884/ \"\u0935\u093f\u0936\u094d\u0935 \u092d\u094d\u0930\u092e\u0923 \u092f\u093e\u0924\u094d\u0930\u0940 \u0938\u0940 \u092a\u0947\u0921\u0930\u0930\u094d\u0938\u0928 \u0925\u094b\u0930 \u0928\u0947\u092a\u093e\u0932\u092e\u093e\"], ''Online Raftar'', Kathmandu, 30 January 2019. <!--accessed 16 January 2020--></ref><ref name=\"GNN TV\">[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OWw4dbfNOxU&feature=youtu.be], ''GNN TV'', Islamabad, 28 December 2018. <!--accessed 16 January 2020--></ref><ref name=\"Oman Daily Observer\">[https://www.omanobserver.om/around-the-world-without-planes/ \"Around the world without planes\"], ''Oman Daily Observer'', Singapore, 14 September 2018. <!--accessed 16 January 2020--></ref>\nNotable outlets that have covered Pedersens quest between 2013 and 2020 include VICE, BBC, Lonely Planet, National Geographic, Forbes, Al Jazeera, The Guardian, News.com.au, The National and ABC.<ref name=\"ABC Radio\">Darmadi, Mala [https://www.abc.net.au/radio-australia/programs/pacificmornings/thor-visit-nauru/11773540 \"Thor visits Nauru on global tour\"], ''ABC'', Melbourne, 7 September 2019. <!--accessed 06 December 2019--></ref>\n\n== Red Cross Red Crescent ==\nPedersen was given a role within the ''Emergency Response Unit (ERU)'' of the ''Red Cross''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://mitrodekors.dk/nyheder/taettere-paa-torbjoern|title=Danish Red Cross|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref> Throughout the year he attended various trainings and became a logistics delegate of the ''ERU'' and towards the end of the 10 months planning period the ''Danish Red Cross'' appointed Pedersen a ''Goodwill Ambassador.''\n\nPedersen holds the following roles and memberships in various societies within the International [[Red Cross Red Crescent Movement]]:\n* ''Goodwill Ambassador of the Danish Red Cross Society''\n* ''Lifetime member of Bahamas Red Cross Society''\n* ''Lifetime member of Kenya Red Cross Society''\n* ''Honorary member of Seychelles Red Cross Society''\n* ''Humanitarian ambassador of Sudanese Red Crescent Society''\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://mitrodekors.dk/nyheder/taettere-paa-torbjoern Danish Red Cross]\n* [http://www.onceuponasaga.dk Once Upon a Saga]\n* [https://www.bws.net/en Blue Water Shipping]\n* [http://www.redsand.dk Red Sand Solutions]\n* [https://www.linkedin.com/in/torbj\u00f8rn-c-pedersen-9a996511/ Linkedin]\n\n[[Category:1978 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Travelers]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Danish tourist, traveller and adventurer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n|name=Torbj\u00f8rn C. Pedersen\n|image=Torbjorn_C._Pedersen_in_Fiji.jpg\n|caption=Pedersen in Fiji, December 2019\n|birth_place=[[Kerteminde]], [[Denmark]]\n|birth_date=19 December 1978<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.onceuponasaga.dk/images/Pictures/_new/254/bula.jpg|title=Torbj\u00f8rn C. Pedersen is nicknamed Thor. In Fiji, December 2019.|website=Once Upon a Saga}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''Torbj\u00f8rn C. \"Thor\" Pedersen''' (born 19 December, 1978) is a Danish traveller and adventurer known for the '''''Once Upon a Saga''''' project: a journey to visit every country in the world without the use of air travel. The project has lasted for over six years, and Pedersen had, {{As of|2020|04|3|lc=y}}, visited 194 of the planned 203 nations.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/onceuponasaga/|title=onceuponasaga|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2020-01-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.onceuponasaga.dk/blog/345-negotiating-the-death-toll|title=Negotiating the death toll|last=Pedersen|first=Torbj\u00f8rn C.|website=www.onceuponasaga.dk|language=en-gb|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/travel/article/around-the-world-without-flying/index.html|title=This man is just 9 countries away from visiting every nation in the world without flying. But he's stuck in Hong Kong due to Covid-19|last=CNN|first=Kate Springer|website=CNN|language=en|access-date=2020-04-29}}</ref>\n\n== Early life ==\nTorbj\u00f8rn Cederl\u00f6f Pedersen was born in Kerteminde, Denmark, to Torben Pedersen (Danish) and Ylva Cederl\u00f6f (Finnish). The family moved to Vancouver, Canada, then to Toronto, Canada, and  after that to New Jersey, USA over a period of six years, before returning to Denmark in 1984 where he spent his childhood growing up in Kerteminde and Bryrup before entering business school at Silkeborg Handelsskole, Silkeborg. Pedersen graduated as a merchant student in 1998 and was drafted to the military later the same year, serving as a royal life guard at the royal palaces throughout Denmark. He was later a UN soldier for half a year in Eritrea and Ethiopia. Following an education in shipping and logistic the Dane worked several years abroad in Libya, Bangladesh, Kazahkstan, Azerbaijan, the United States and other countries. When travelling abroad, Torbj\u00f8rn is nicknamed Thor.\n\n== Once Upon a Saga ==\nIn 2013, Pedersen began planning a project which aimed at visiting every country in the world in a single unbroken journey explicitly without the use of air transport.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lonelyplanet.com/news/2016/12/30/travelling-world-no-planes/|title=This man is travelling the world without ever getting on a plane|last=Planet|first=Lonely|website=Lonely Planet News|language=en|access-date=2019-05-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/leifwalcutt/2017/02/14/around-the-world-by-container-ship-one-mans-quest-to-visit-every-country/|title=Around The World By Container Ship: One Man's Quest To Visit Every Country|last=Walcutt|first=Leif|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2019-05-18}}</ref> [[Graham Hughes]] holds the world record of fastest visiting all countries by public surface transport, according to [[Guinness World Records]]. Hughes was however permitted to fly home to Britain twice during his journey, as long as he returned to the same airport in order to continue his journey. To visit every country in the world, in one single journey, without catching a single flight is something that has never been done before.<ref name=\"The National\">Leve, Andy [https://amp.thenational.ae/lifestyle/travel/torbjorn-pedersen-the-man-on-a-mission-to-visit-every-country-in-the-world-without-taking-a-single-flight-1.907263 \"Torbjorn Pedersen: the man on a mission to visit every country in the world, without taking a single flight\"], ''The National'', Abu Dhabi, 7 September 2019. <!--accessed 08 January 2020--></ref>\n\nThrough the project Pedersen intends to reach every country without flying, while promoting every country and the world in a positive way.\n\nOn 10 October, 2013 at 10:10am (10/10,10:10) '''''Once Upon a Saga''''' began at Dybb\u00f8l M\u00f8lle in Southern Denmark. Soon after Pedersen crossed into Germany by train and had, in January 2020, reached 193 of the intended 203 countries<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.onceuponasaga.dk/blog/330-mv-kota-hakim-passenger-no-1-reaching-marshall-islands-the-hard-way|title=MV \"Kota Hakim\" \u2013 passenger no. 1 (reaching Marshall Islands the hard way)|last=Pedersen|first=Torj\u00f8rn|date=2019-12-30|work=Once Upon a Saga|access-date=2020-01-01|language=en-GB}}</ref> on all six inhabited continents without returning home.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vice.com/en_us/article/8qgv3k/kakovo-eto-povidat-mir-prakticheski-besplatno-puteshestvuya-na-kontejnernyh-sudah|title=What It's Like to See the World for Almost No Money by Traveling on Container Ships|last=Pearl|first=Mike|date=2016-12-12|website=Vice|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2014/dec/14/wanderlust-viking-cheap-travel-aeroplane-free-visit-every-country|title=Wanderlust Viking: my aeroplane-free aim to visit every country on \u00a312 a day|last=Russell|first=Helen|date=2014-12-14|work=The Guardian|access-date=2019-05-18|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref>\n\nHe was originally expected to complete the project and return to Denmark again in 2020 after visiting his last country, the Maldives, in October 2020.<ref name=\"Midtjyllands Avis\">Andersen, Mette [https://www.midtjyllandsavis.dk/artikel/1c992215-593b-4bab-aa1b-9df8244f6693/ \"Eventyrer har lang vej hjem\"], ''Midtjyllands Avis'', Silkeborg, 4 January 2020. <!--accessed 08 January 2020--></ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Travel/danish-man-travels-world-20-day/story?id=26995531|title=How This Man Travels the World on Just $20 a Day|website=ABC News|language=en|access-date=2019-05-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.news.com.au/travel/world-travel/danish-traveller-torbjorn-c-pedersen-travels-the-world-on-just-20-a-day/news-story/556c52b6292ff2be7b8840be1ba94cd2|title=How to travel the world without using one plane|date=2014-11-17|website=NewsComAu|access-date=2019-05-18}}</ref> However, {{As of|2020|April|lc=y}}, he has been stuck in Hong Kong for several months due to the [[COVID-19 epidemic]].<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nThe long journey has earned Pedersen media coverage in more than 100 countries so far.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.onceuponasaga.dk/press|title=Press|last=Salquist|first=Ann-Christina|date=2014-12-14|work=Once Upon a Saga|access-date=2020-01-01|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref name=\"Borneo Bulletin\">[https://borneobulletin.com.bn/danish-globetrotter-finds-bruneians-absolute-sweethearts-2/ \"Danish globetrotter finds Bruneians \u2018absolute sweethearts\u2019\"], ''Borneo Bulletin'', Bandar Seri Begawan, 20 July 2019. <!--accessed 16 January 2020--></ref><ref name=\"Kuwait Bazaar\">[https://bazaar.town/thor-once-upon-a-saga/ \"ONLY NINETEEN MORE THOR!\"], ''Kuwait Bazaar'', Kuwait, 1 July 2019. <!--accessed 16 January 2020--></ref><ref name=\"The New Paper\">[https://www.tnp.sg/news/singapore/he-journeys-across-world-without-flying-red-cross \"He journeys across the world without flying for the Red Cross\"], ''The New Paper'', Singapore, 21 June 2019. <!--accessed 16 January 2020--></ref><ref name=\"CNTraveler India\">[https://www.cntraveller.in/story/name-thor-hes-travelling-around-world-without-flying/ \"His name is Thor and he\u2019s travelling around the world without flying\"], ''Cond\u00e9 Nast Traveler India'', Mumbai, 2 February 2019. <!--accessed 16 January 2020--></ref><ref name=\"Online Raftar\">[https://www.onlineraftar.com/2019/01/30/26884/ \"\u0935\u093f\u0936\u094d\u0935 \u092d\u094d\u0930\u092e\u0923 \u092f\u093e\u0924\u094d\u0930\u0940 \u0938\u0940 \u092a\u0947\u0921\u0930\u0930\u094d\u0938\u0928 \u0925\u094b\u0930 \u0928\u0947\u092a\u093e\u0932\u092e\u093e\"], ''Online Raftar'', Kathmandu, 30 January 2019. <!--accessed 16 January 2020--></ref><ref name=\"GNN TV\">[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OWw4dbfNOxU&feature=youtu.be], ''GNN TV'', Islamabad, 28 December 2018. <!--accessed 16 January 2020--></ref><ref name=\"Oman Daily Observer\">[https://www.omanobserver.om/around-the-world-without-planes/ \"Around the world without planes\"], ''Oman Daily Observer'', Singapore, 14 September 2018. <!--accessed 16 January 2020--></ref>\nNotable outlets that have covered Pedersens quest between 2013 and 2020 include VICE, BBC, Lonely Planet, National Geographic, Forbes, Al Jazeera, The Guardian, News.com.au, The National and ABC.<ref name=\"ABC Radio\">Darmadi, Mala [https://www.abc.net.au/radio-australia/programs/pacificmornings/thor-visit-nauru/11773540 \"Thor visits Nauru on global tour\"], ''ABC'', Melbourne, 7 September 2019. <!--accessed 06 December 2019--></ref>\n\n== Red Cross Red Crescent ==\nPedersen was given a role within the ''Emergency Response Unit (ERU)'' of the ''Red Cross''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://mitrodekors.dk/nyheder/taettere-paa-torbjoern|title=Danish Red Cross|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref> Throughout the year he attended various trainings and became a logistics delegate of the ''ERU'' and towards the end of the 10 months planning period the ''Danish Red Cross'' appointed Pedersen a ''Goodwill Ambassador.''\n\nPedersen holds the following roles and memberships in various societies within the International [[Red Cross Red Crescent Movement]]:\n* ''Goodwill Ambassador of the Danish Red Cross Society''\n* ''Lifetime member of Bahamas Red Cross Society''\n* ''Lifetime member of Kenya Red Cross Society''\n* ''Honorary member of Seychelles Red Cross Society''\n* ''Humanitarian ambassador of Sudanese Red Crescent Society''\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://mitrodekors.dk/nyheder/taettere-paa-torbjoern Danish Red Cross]\n* [http://www.onceuponasaga.dk Once Upon a Saga]\n* [https://www.bws.net/en Blue Water Shipping]\n* [http://www.redsand.dk Red Sand Solutions]\n* [https://www.linkedin.com/in/torbj\u00f8rn-c-pedersen-9a996511/ Linkedin]\n\n[[Category:1978 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Travelers]]\n", "name_user": "John B123", "label": "safe", "comment": "Fixed cite errors", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Torbj%C3%B8rn_C._Pedersen"}
{"title_page": "Helianthemum nummularium", "text_new": "{{short description|Species of flowering plants in the rock rose family Cistaceae}}\n{{speciesbox\n|image = Sonnenr\u00f6schen.jpg\n|image_caption = ''Helianthemum nummularium'' subsp. ''glabrum''\n|genus = Helianthemum\n|species = nummularium\n|authority = ([[Carl Linnaeus|L.]]) [[Philip Miller|Mill.]]\n}}\n[[File:Helianthemum nummularium MHNT.BOT.2007.43.43.jpg|thumb|''Helianthemum nummularium'' - [[MHNT]]]]\n\n'''''Helianthemum nummularium''''' (known as '''common rock-rose'''<ref name=BSBI07>{{cite web |title=BSBI List 2007 |publisher=Botanical Society of Britain and Ireland |url=http://www.bsbi.org.uk/BSBIList2007.xls |format=xls |accessdate=2014-10-17 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6VqJ46atN?url=http://www.bsbi.org.uk/BSBIList2007.xls |archivedate=2015-01-25 }}</ref>) is a species of [[Helianthemum|rock-rose]] ([[Cistaceae]]), native to most of [[Europe]].\n\n==Description==\nIt  is an evergreen trailing plant with loose terminal clusters of bright yellow, saucer-shaped flowers. In the flower centre is a tight cluster of orange stamens, which are sensitive to the touch, and spread outwards to reveal the tall stigma in the middle. The plant is common on chalk downs, and occasional in other grasslands, always on dry, base-rich soil. The wild species has yellow flowers, but garden varieties range from white through yellow to deep red.\n\nThough the individual blooms are short-lived, the plant produces a mass of flowers through the summer. It needs a dry, sunny place, like a south-facing rockery or meadow. As the Latin name ''Helianthemum'' suggests, these are sun-flowers. This is a good nectar source for bees and there are several species of small beetle that feed on the foliage. Common rock-rose is also the food plant for the larvae of several species of moth and butterfly such as the [[Silver-studded blue|silver-studded blue (''Plebejus argus).'']]\n\nIt flowers from May until July.\n\n==Taxonomy==\n===Subspecies===\nThere are eight [[subspecies]]:\n*''Helianthemum nummularium'' subsp. ''nummularium''. Widespread.\n*''Helianthemum nummularium'' subsp. ''berterianum''. Italy, southeast France.\n*''Helianthemum nummularium'' subsp. ''glabrum''. Central and southern Europe.\n*''Helianthemum nummularium'' subsp. ''grandiflorum''. Central and southern Europe.\n*''Helianthemum nummularium'' subsp. ''obscurum''. Eastern Europe.\n*''Helianthemum nummularium'' subsp. ''pyrenaicum''. Pyrenees.\n*''Helianthemum nummularium'' subsp. ''semiglabrum''. Italy, southeast France.\n*''Helianthemum nummularium'' subsp. ''tomentosum''. Southern Europe.\n\n=== Gallery ===\n<gallery>\nImage:Helianthemum alpestre0.jpg| <!-- please, do not worry about the file name -->\nImage:Sonnenr\u00f6schen.jpg\nImage:Sonnenr\u00f6schen02.jpg\n</gallery>\n\n=== subsp. ''grandiflorum'' (Scop.) Schinz & Thell. ===\n<gallery>\nImage:Helianthemum grandiflorum a1.jpg\nImage:Helianthemum grandiflorum a2.jpg\n</gallery>\n\n=== subsp. ''nummularium'' ===\n<gallery>\nImage:Helianthemum_nummularium1.jpg\nImage:Solv\u00e4nda.jpg\n</gallery>\n\n=== subsp. ''obscurum'' (\u010celak.) Holub) ===\n<gallery>\nImage:Helianthemum_nummularium_subsp_obscurum_260807.jpg|''H. nummularium'' subsp. ''obscurum''<br />Germany - Schw\u00e4bisch Fr\u00e4nkische Waldberge\nImage:Helianthemum_nummularium_subsp_obscurum_260807a.jpg|''H. nummularium'' subsp. ''obscurum''<br />Germany - Schw\u00e4bisch Fr\u00e4nkische Waldberge\nImage:Helianthemum_nummularium_subsp_obscurum_300907.jpg|''H. nummularium'' subsp. ''obscurum''<br />Germany - Schw\u00e4bische Alb\nImage:Helianthemum nummularium subsp obscurum 220608.jpg|''H. nummularium'' subsp. ''obscurum''<br />Germany - Schw\u00e4bische Alb\nImage:Helianthemum nummularifolium1.jpg\nImage:Helianthemum nummularifolium0.jpg\n</gallery>\n\n=== Pink-flowered cultivars ===\n<gallery>\nImage:Prolecne-perene-2.jpg\nImage:Perene-roze.jpg\n</gallery>\n\n=== Illustrations ===\n<gallery>\nImage:Helianthemum vulgare Sturm51.jpg\nImage:Helianthemum vulgare flowerdiagram.png|flower diagram\n</gallery>\n\n=== Unclassified images of ''Helianthemum nummularium'' ===\n<gallery>\nImage:Helianthemum nummularium2.jpg\nImage:Helianthemum nummularium2.JPG\nImage:Helianthemum nummularium - leafs (aka).jpg\n</gallery>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n*[http://rbg-web2.rbge.org.uk/cgi-bin/nph-readbtree.pl/feout?FAMILY_XREF=&GENUS_XREF=Helianthemum&SPECIES_XREF=nummularium&TAXON_NAME_XREF=&RANK= Flora Europaea: ''Helianthemum nummularium'']\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q164232}}\n\n[[Category:Helianthemum|numularium]]\n[[Category:Flora of Lebanon]]\n[[Category:Flora of Western Asia]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Species of flowering plants in the rock rose family Cistaceae}}\n{{speciesbox\n|image = Sonnenr\u00f6schen.jpg\n|image_caption = ''Helianthemum nummularium'' subsp. ''glabrum''\n|genus = Helianthemum\n|species = nummularium\n|authority = ([[Carl Linnaeus|L.]]) [[Philip Miller|Mill.]]\n}}\n[[File:Helianthemum nummularium MHNT.BOT.2007.43.43.jpg|thumb|''Helianthemum nummularium'' - [[MHNT]]]]\n\n'''''Helianthemum nummularium''''' (known as '''common rock-rose'''<ref name=BSBI07>{{cite web |title=BSBI List 2007 |publisher=Botanical Society of Britain and Ireland |url=http://www.bsbi.org.uk/BSBIList2007.xls |format=xls |accessdate=2014-10-17 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6VqJ46atN?url=http://www.bsbi.org.uk/BSBIList2007.xls |archivedate=2015-01-25 }}</ref>) is a species of [[Helianthemum|rock-rose]] ([[Cistaceae]]), native to most of [[Europe]].\n\n==Description==\nIt  is an evergreen trailing plant with loose terminal clusters of bright yellow, saucer-shaped flowers. In the flower centre is a tight cluster of orange stamens, which are sensitive to the touch, and spread outwards to reveal the tall stigma in the middle. The plant is common on chalk downs, and occasional in other grasslands, always on dry, base-rich soil. The wild species has yellow flowers, but garden varieties range from white through yellow to deep red.\n\nThough the individual blooms are short-lived, the plant produces a mass of flowers through the summer. It needs a dry, sunny place, like a south-facing rockery or meadow. As the Latin name ''Helianthemum'' suggests, these are sun-flowers. This is a good nectar source for bees and there are several species of small beetle that feed on the foliage. Common rock-rose is also the food plant for the larvae of several species of moth and butterfly such as the [[Silver-studded blue|silver-studded blue (''Plebejus argus).'']]\n\nIt flowers from May until July.\n\n==Subspecies==\n\nThere are eight [[subspecies]]:\n*''Helianthemum nummularium'' subsp. ''nummularium''. Widespread.\n*''Helianthemum nummularium'' subsp. ''berterianum''. Italy, southeast France.\n*''Helianthemum nummularium'' subsp. ''glabrum''. Central and southern Europe.\n*''Helianthemum nummularium'' subsp. ''grandiflorum''. Central and southern Europe.\n*''Helianthemum nummularium'' subsp. ''obscurum''. Eastern Europe.\n*''Helianthemum nummularium'' subsp. ''pyrenaicum''. Pyrenees.\n*''Helianthemum nummularium'' subsp. ''semiglabrum''. Italy, southeast France.\n*''Helianthemum nummularium'' subsp. ''tomentosum''. Southern Europe.\n\n==Images==\n<gallery>\nImage:Helianthemum alpestre0.jpg| <!-- please, do not worry about the file name -->\nImage:Sonnenr\u00f6schen.jpg\nImage:Sonnenr\u00f6schen02.jpg\n</gallery>\n\n==subsp. ''grandiflorum'' (Scop.) Schinz & Thell. ==\n<gallery>\nImage:Helianthemum grandiflorum a1.jpg\nImage:Helianthemum grandiflorum a2.jpg\n</gallery>\n\n== subsp. ''nummularium'' ==\n<gallery>\nImage:Helianthemum_nummularium1.jpg\nImage:Solv\u00e4nda.jpg\n</gallery>\n\n==subsp. ''obscurum'' (\u010celak.) Holub) ==\n<gallery>\nImage:Helianthemum_nummularium_subsp_obscurum_260807.jpg|''H. nummularium'' subsp. ''obscurum''<br />Germany - Schw\u00e4bisch Fr\u00e4nkische Waldberge\nImage:Helianthemum_nummularium_subsp_obscurum_260807a.jpg|''H. nummularium'' subsp. ''obscurum''<br />Germany - Schw\u00e4bisch Fr\u00e4nkische Waldberge\nImage:Helianthemum_nummularium_subsp_obscurum_300907.jpg|''H. nummularium'' subsp. ''obscurum''<br />Germany - Schw\u00e4bische Alb\nImage:Helianthemum nummularium subsp obscurum 220608.jpg|''H. nummularium'' subsp. ''obscurum''<br />Germany - Schw\u00e4bische Alb\nImage:Helianthemum nummularifolium1.jpg\nImage:Helianthemum nummularifolium0.jpg\n</gallery>\n\n== Pink-flowered cultivars ==\n<gallery>\nImage:Prolecne-perene-2.jpg\nImage:Perene-roze.jpg\n</gallery>\n\n== Illustrations ==\n<gallery>\nImage:Helianthemum vulgare Sturm51.jpg\nImage:Helianthemum vulgare flowerdiagram.png|flower diagram\n</gallery>\n\n== Unclassified images of ''Helianthemum nummularium'' ==\n<gallery>\nImage:Helianthemum nummularium2.jpg\nImage:Helianthemum nummularium2.JPG\nImage:Helianthemum nummularium - leafs (aka).jpg\n</gallery>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n*[http://rbg-web2.rbge.org.uk/cgi-bin/nph-readbtree.pl/feout?FAMILY_XREF=&GENUS_XREF=Helianthemum&SPECIES_XREF=nummularium&TAXON_NAME_XREF=&RANK= Flora Europaea: ''Helianthemum nummularium'']\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q164232}}\n\n[[Category:Helianthemum|numularium]]\n[[Category:Flora of Lebanon]]\n[[Category:Flora of Western Asia]]\n", "name_user": "Manudouz", "label": "safe", "comment": "Subsections.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Helianthemum_nummularium"}
